cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with machine learning and computer vision, specifically image semantic segmentation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm involves neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the algorithm is in the field of geography, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) to some extent, as it deals with image-level categorical labels, which could be considered a form of text data, hence it could also fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
